        "cooked": "<p><strong>Feature Request: Implement Differentiation of ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù and ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù States for Outgoing Calls on Signal Desktop</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Summary:</strong><br>\nTo enhance the user experience and provide clearer call status information on Signal Desktop, I propose implementing a differentiation between the ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù and ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù states for outgoing calls, similar to the functionality available on Signal for Android.</p>\n<p><strong>Background:</strong><br>\nOn Signal for Android, when making an outgoing call, users can see distinct statuses: ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù (when the call is being initiated but the recipient has not yet been alerted) and ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù (when the recipient‚Äôs device is actively ringing). This distinction provides valuable feedback to the caller about the current state of the call. Currently, Signal Desktop only displays ‚ÄúRinging,‚Äù regardless of whether the call is still being initiated or if the recipient‚Äôs device is actually ringing.</p>\n<p><strong>Current Behavior:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>When initiating an outgoing call from Signal Desktop, the status displayed is always ‚ÄúRinging,‚Äù even if the recipient‚Äôs device has not yet started ringing.</li>\n<li>This can cause confusion for users, as they may not be aware of whether the call is still connecting or if the recipient‚Äôs device is actually ringing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Proposed Feature:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Implement ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù Status:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Display ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù on the call screen when the call is being initiated but the recipient‚Äôs device has not yet started ringing. This status indicates that the system is attempting to connect to the recipient.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Retain ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù Status:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Display ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù only when the recipient‚Äôs device is actively ringing, indicating that the call has successfully reached the recipient‚Äôs device.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Clearer Call Status:</strong> Provides users with precise information about the current state of their outgoing call, reducing confusion and improving the overall calling experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Consistency Across Platforms:</strong> Aligns Signal Desktop with the functionality of Signal for Android, offering a consistent user experience across devices.</li>\n<li><strong>Improved User Feedback:</strong> Users can better understand if there are connection issues or if the recipient is simply not answering.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Implementation Concept:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Modify the call status display logic on Signal Desktop to introduce a ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù state.</li>\n<li>Transition from ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù to ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù once the recipient‚Äôs device starts ringing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>User Scenario:</strong><br>\nA user initiates a call from Signal Desktop and sees ‚ÄúCalling,‚Äù indicating that the call is being set up. Once the recipient‚Äôs device begins to ring, the status updates to ‚ÄúRinging,‚Äù providing clear feedback that the call is now alerting the recipient.</p>\n<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong><br>\nDifferentiating between ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù and ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù states for outgoing calls on Signal Desktop will significantly improve the clarity and usability of the calling feature. This enhancement addresses user feedback and aligns with Signal‚Äôs goal of providing an intuitive and seamless communication experience.</p>",
