        "id": 274122,
        "name": "",
        "username": "oeoeb",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/oeoeb/{size}/41174_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-27T16:37:27.466Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-username=\"carlosuno\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"61621\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/71c47a/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> carlosuno:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>On Signal for Android [‚Ä¶] This distinction provides valuable feedback to the caller about the current state of the call.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I use signal most often on Android and most of my friends use Android (Europe).<br>\nLet me tell you: The current distinction between ‚ÄúCalling‚Äù and ‚ÄúRinging‚Äù is no enough so that regular users understand this.</p>\n<p>I estimate 50% to 70% of the calls I receive never ring on my phone: People are not aware that they have to wait until the ‚Äúringing‚Äù phase for the phone to actually ring. If this is due to spotty wifi / reception on the recipient or what else, I don‚Äôt know. But it happens A LOT for A LOT of my Signal using friends and family.</p>\n<p>And I can not blame them:<br>\nUX for a telephone connection: Either there‚Äôs the busy tone, or there‚Äôs the ringback tone. During the ringback tone, the called phone rings.</p>\n<p>UX for Signal: Busy tone = busy. Ringback tone: either trying to establish a connection (while the phone is not ringing) or ringing (and the phone rings).</p>\n<p>I am an avid Signal user since 2015. My clearest feedback is: People don‚Äôt get this. It would be good to fix.</p>\n<p>Thanks for considering</p>",
